    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName>, <date>May 6<hi rend="sup"
                        >th</hi> 1857</date></p>
            <p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>, <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear friend:</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I <sic>dont</sic> know <sic>wether</sic> you can<lb/> use the
                enclosed article and I am not hurt<lb/> in the least if you tell me it is not worth<lb/>
                <del>a dam</del>. I feel that I have not looked<lb/> around with a sufficiently
                searching mind<lb/> to make a complete and correct report.<lb/> But I believe that I
                have told the<lb/> truth. Should you decide to print it, then<lb/> I wish you would
                correct my bad English.<lb/> Although I generally do not do it, but this<lb/> case
                you may be at liberty to add or leave off<lb/> as you see fit, for I can readily see
                the<lb/> lack of better <del>
                    <add>?</add>
                </del> comprehension. I should have<lb/> added that for the first time I preached
                here<lb/> in the German language on <date>Rosh Hashannah</date>.<lb/> The
                congregation might have gotten some<lb/> new members. The Bavarian congregation<lb/>
                followed this example at once. But I <sic>dont</sic><lb/> want to talk about myself
                nor do I wish<lb/> to go into details. In the near future I hope<lb/> to send you an
                entirely different contribution</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">-2-</p>
            <p>which might have more value.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I am happy, honest to God happy<lb/> that you continued the Occident
                and I<lb/> am only sorry that I cannot do anything<lb/> to further its
                distribution.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">When you come to <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> I want you to
                see my Seferim. Especially<lb/> | | | ask for my <add>פחד יצחק</add>
                <add>?</add>
                <add>Pahad Yitzhak</add>, the great and rare<lb/> talmudic REAL (ANAL?) LEXICON
                (dictionary).<lb/> Only a few copies are in existence and none are<lb/> sold in book
                stores. <persName>Dr. Zunz</persName>, <persName>Sachs</persName> and<lb/>
                <persName>Rappoport</persName> paid 30¢ for a copy. <del>It will be<lb/>of gre</del>
                It will greatly assist you in your<lb/> work and you get 30% off the list
                price.<lb/> You need not spend a cent and I can in this<lb/> manner not only pay off
                my debt, but also the $3.— for the new subscriptions of the Occident.<lb/> And
                moreover I would consider it a favor,<lb/> for which I promise to be thankful in
                later<lb/> years when I God helping, will find myself<lb/> in better financial
                strength.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your very truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Isidor Bush</persName>
            </p>
            <p>He probably meant $</p>
        </body>
